post_text:
Segue welcomes our new staff 2020-2021

Hey Segue families, my name is Chris Croteau and I am excited to be the new music teacher at Segue Institute for Learning! I was born and raised in North Kingstown, RI but went on to earn my Bachelors of Music at Loyola University, New Orleans and my Masters in the Art of Teaching K-12 music at Memphis University. I am eager to share my passion for music with all my students this year and hope to inspire them to express themselves and create.

Segue le da la Bienvenida a nuestro nuevo personal 2020-2021

Hey Segue familias, mi nombre es Chris Croteau y estoy contento de ser el nuevo profesor de música en Segue Institute for Learning! Nací y crecí en North Kingstown, RI, pero obtuve mis licenciaturas en música en la Universidad Loyola, Nueva Orleans y mi Maestría en Arte de Enseñar música K-12 en la Universidad de Memphis. Estoy anheloso por compartir mi pasión por la música con todos mis alumnos este año y espero inspirarlos a expresarse y crear.

Progreso Latino is sharing a COVID-19 Update.
August 24 at 11:00 AM ·

The Progreso Latino Food Pantry will be open Today, Monday,(8/24/2020) from 9 AM-12 PM at Progreso Latino, 626 Broad Street, CF, RI (401) 365-4010. EACH FAMILY WILL RECEIVE 1 BOX. Thank you for your understanding. We will distribute Produce Boxes with fruits and vegetables (22 pounds). We will also distribute FEMA Federal Emergency Management Agency Family Boxes containing 10 meals and more than 20 items such as cereals, milk, rice, beans, canned goods, fruit cups and snacks (14 pounds). The Progreso Latino Food Pantry is for Central Falls residents and immigrant families in RI, regardless of citizenship or immigration status. NO ID Required. NO Appointment Needed. Handicap Accessible. Masks are required. Progreso Latino is a member agency of the Rhode Island Community Food Bank which provides the food for the food pantry and is funded by the Rhode Island Foundation.

Progreso Latino is sharing a COVID-19 Update.
August 11 at 8:53 PM ·

Progreso Latino will distribute 600 Produce Boxes and 400 Family Boxes (18,800 pounds). TOMORROW, Wednesday,(8/12/2020), 9 AM-12 PM at Progreso Latino, 626 Broad Street, CF, RI (401) 365-4010. The FIRST 440 families will receive a Farm Fresh Rhode Island Box. Each box contains 22 pounds of vegetables, fruit, cheese and milk. The NEXT 160 families will receive a 22 pound Produce Box with fruits and vegetables. The last 400 families will receive FEMA Federal Emergency Management Agency Family Boxes containing 10 meals and more than 20 items such as cereals, milk, rice, beans, canned goods, fruit cups and snacks. The Progreso Latino Food Pantry is for Central Falls residents and immigrant families in RI, regardless of citizenship or immigration status. NO ID Required. NO Appointment Needed. Handicap Accessible. Masks are required. Progreso Latino is a member agency of the Rhode Island Community Food Bank which provides the food for the food pantry and is funded by the Rhode Island Foundation.

post_text:
Food Supply Distribution at McCoy Stadium

The City of Pawtucket is partnering with Ocean State Job Lot, the Elisha Project, and the Pawtucket Red Sox to provide essential food supplies to residents of Pawtucket and Central Falls.
The distribution of food supplies will be on Friday, June 19 at McCoy Stadium, from 8:30 am to NOON or until supplies last.

Please be advised that this is a mobile distribution via car vehicles only and no walk ups will be serviced at this location.

We are asking that the following protocols be followed:
1. Approach on Ashton Street (where the statue of PAWS is located.)

2. To minimize personal contact, please limit vehicles to 2 people.

3. We are asking that NO ONE get out of their vehicles for any reason during this distribution of supplies.

4. Open the trunk or back seat for placement of items.

5. One family will be serviced per vehicle. You cannot pick up items for other families.

post_text:
Attention students! Get up to $750 to take a Math or ELA class this Summer:
If you are going to be in 9th or 12th grade in September, or if you have just graduated from high school (Class of 2020!) sign up here to take a fully online Math or ELA class for eight weeks from June 29 - August 21 and get paid up to $750 ($250 for 9th graders and $750 for 12th graders) for completing assignments! You can choose to attend either a morning or afternoon virtual session every day for 30 minutes with the whole class, and will then complete assignments in small groups and independently. The Math courses will focus on making sure you are caught up and ready for class in September, and the ELA courses will be reading comedian Trevor Noah’s Born a Crime.

https://ride.gosignmeup.com/Public/Course/Browse

Rhode Island KIDS COUNT
June 12 at 2:26 PM ·

Disparities in child poverty are severe and persistent — and can be fixed with smart, intentional policies.

Proud that equity is the *first* recommendation as a way to work toward eliminating child poverty here at home in RI: bit.ly/2MOrEij #childpovertyRI

🚩 The publication highlights the serious concern that COVID-19 will exacerbate horrifying disparities.

🚩 Historical racism in policies are called out in the publication, as well as the legacy of inequality they built. Purposefully constructed systems created — and continue to uphold —economic inequity.

In the midst of a pandemic, our Senior Policy Analyst Paige Clausius-Parka wrote this incredibly important publication — you did a beautiful job.

The Economic Progress Institute United Way of Rhode Island Housing Network of Rhode Island Nirva LaFortune for Providence City Council, Ward 3 Rhode Island Community Food Bank Rhode Island Foundation

In the midst of a pandemic, our Senior Policy Analyst Paige Clausius-Parka wrote this incredibly important publication — you did a beautiful job.

The Economic Progress Institute United Way of Rhode Island Housing Network of Rhode Island Nirva LaFortune for Providence City Council, Ward 3 Rhode Island Community Food Bank Rhode Island Foundation

Segue Institute for Learning
April 20 at 10:36 AM ·

The city of Pawtucket is partnering with Ocean StateJob Lot to provide milk to residence of Central Falls and Pawtucket. Today , Monday April 20th at McCoy Stadium from 8:30am until supplies last .
Mobile distribution via car vehicles only. No walk ups. 2 people per car and we advice to open car back seat or trunk for minimum contact. You cannot pick up for another family or get out your car. Thank you and stay safe

La ciudad de Pawtucket y las tiendas de Ocean State Job Lot estarán entregando leche a los residentes de Central Falls y Pawtucket. Hoy, Lunes 20 de Abril en el Estadio McCoy a partir de las 8:30am hasta que se acaben las leches. Esto será una distribución Mobil solo a personas en carros. No se les repartirá a las persona que vayan caminando. Para minimizar el contacto con la gente, se les repartirá a las personas con un mínimo de dos personas por carro y tendrán que abrir la puerta del asiento de atrás o del baúl para la entrega. No podrán recoger para otra gente. También les pedimos que no salgan de sus carros. Gracias y manténgase a salvo.

post_text:
Greetings 6th & 7th Graders,

Beginning Monday, you MUST check your nest (advisory) google classroom every school day. In that google classroom, you will find:
• A Daily News Question that you MUST answer for attendance purposes
• To get credit for each content class, you must complete the assigned work and TURN IT IN.
• An Agenda for the day with a checklist to help you stay organized
Reach out to your advisor if you have any questions!

Saludos estudiantes del 6to y 7mo grado

Empezando el Lunes, ustedes DEBEN chequear su nest (advisory) google classroom/salón virtual de google en la computadora todos los dias. En el salón virtual de google, podrás encontrar lo siguiente:
• Una Pregunta diaria que TIENES que responder por motivos de asistencia
• Para obtener un crédio en cada clase, tienes que completar el trabajo asignado en linea y DEVOLVERLO
• Una agenda del día con un lista de cosas para hacer y asi te puedas mantener organizado
Comunicate con tu asesor con cualquier pregunta.

Delia Rodriguez-Masjoan
March 26 at 2:13 PM ·

~BILINGUAL MESSAGE~
With more Rhode Islanders staying home during the coronavirus crisis, this is a great opportunity to fill out the 2020 Census.

The Census determines how much money Rhode Island receives in federal funding for things like health care that could have a major impact on our ability to handle crises like the coronavirus outbreak.
Go to this page now!

~SPANISH~
Con más habitantes de Rhode Island quedándose en casa durante la crisis del coronavirus, esta es una gran oportunidad para completar el Censo 2020.

El Censo determina cuánto dinero recibe Rhode Island en fondos federales para cosas como la atención médica que podrían tener un gran impacto en nuestra capacidad para manejar crisis como el brote de coronavirus.

¡Vaya a esta página ya!

Segue's Student Council lead by our one and only Ms Perry will be doing a 50/50 raffle until the end of August.
50/50 raffle is when the winner of the raffle wins half of the "jackpot". For example, if the jackpot is $100, the winner would get $50.
Please share and make sure you get your tickets for a chance to win!! Contact Ms Perry for tickets

Nuestro Concejo Estudiantil liderado por nuestra unica Ms Perry tendra una rifa 50/50 durante el mes de Agosto .
Una rifa de 50/50 es cuando el ganador se lleva la mitad de lo ganado. Por ejemplo: si las ganacias son $100, el ganador se llevara la mitad que es $50
Por favor compartir este mensaje y asegurate de comprar tickets para tener la oportunidad de ganar!! Contactese con la Sta. Perry para comprar tickets.

post_text:
CCRI dental clinic offers free exams, teeth cleaning

WARWICK -- Rhode Islanders can receive a free teeth cleaning and oral health examination during the spring semester at Community College of Rhode Island’s dental hygiene clinic in Lincoln.

Appointments are two hours and can be scheduled Monday through Friday for 8 or 10 a.m. or 1 and 3 p.m. Night appointments are available at 6 p.m. on Tuesdays and Thursdays. The clinic will see patients through April.

Patients do not need any type of insurance to receive treatment.

Call 401-333-7250 to schedule an appointment. The clinic is located in Room 1120 at Flanagan campus, 1762 Louquisett Pike, Lincoln.
